# Shell Command Best Practices

## Avoid Unnecessary `cd`

Use the `working_directory` parameter instead:

```zig
// ❌ BAD
Shell.run("cd /path && command")

// ✅ GOOD
Shell.run("command", .{ .working_directory = "/path" })
```

## Avoid Unnecessary `echo`

Commands provide their own output:

```bash
# ❌ BAD
command && echo "Done"

# ✅ GOOD
command
```

## Keep Commands Simple

Only chain commands when dependencies exist:

```bash
# ❌ BAD
cd dir && echo "Building" && make && echo "Done"

# ✅ GOOD
make  # Use working_directory parameter
```
